  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 230&deg;C/ 210&deg;C (fan)/ 450&deg;F/ Gas 8</p>\r\n<p>Cut all the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-size pieces&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Add&nbsp;them to a baking tray, drizzle with 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\">&nbsp;[4 tbsp]</span>&nbsp;<strong>vegetable oil</strong> and season generously&nbsp;with <strong>salt&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Put them in the oven for an initial 25 min</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/459_step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/459_step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/459_step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/459_step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/459_step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel&nbsp;and finely slice the <strong>red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Deseed the <strong>yellow</strong>&nbsp;<strong>pepper<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Lato; font-size: 15px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/459_step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/459_step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/459_step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/459_step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/459_step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan with a drizzle of&nbsp;<strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium-low heat&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>onion</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> with a big pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cook for 15-20 min or until softened and caramelised</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/459_step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/459_step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/459_step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/459_step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/459_step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut the<strong>&nbsp;mini chorizo</strong> in half</p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>garlic</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop the <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/459_step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/459_step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/459_step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/459_step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/459_step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once&nbsp;the <strong>potatoes</strong> are very nearly cooked, remove the tray from the oven, turn the potatoes and scatter the <strong>chorizo</strong> amongst them</p>\r\n<p>Return the tray to the oven for a further 10 min or until the potatoes are crisp and the chorizo is hot</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/459_step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/459_step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/459_step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/459_step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/459_step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a separate pan (large enough to fit 4 <span class=\"text-danger\">[8]</span><strong>&nbsp;eggs</strong> in, and preferably non-stick) with a matching lid, with 1 tbsp&nbsp;<span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span>&nbsp;<strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-low heat</p>\r\n<p>Tip:&nbsp;shake your eggs before cracking for a perfectly-centred yolk</p>\r\n<p>Once&nbsp;hot, add the <strong>eggs</strong>, cover and cook for 3 min</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/459_step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/459_step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/459_step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/459_step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/459_step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> to the onion and pepper pan and reduce the heat to low (adding more olive oil if too dry)</p>\r\n<p>Stir in&nbsp;the<strong>&nbsp;apple cider vinegar</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span>&nbsp;<strong>sugar</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cook for a further 2 min, then remove from the heat and season with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/459_step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/459_step-7-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/459_step-7-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/459_step-7-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/459_step-7-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Stir most of the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>parsley</strong> through the pepper and onion mixture - this is your<strong> relish</strong></p>\r\n<p>Serve the <strong>eggs</strong> over the <strong>chorizo</strong> and <strong>potatoes</strong></p>\r\n<p>Serve the&nbsp;<strong>relish</strong> to the side and garnish with the remaining<strong> parsley</strong></p>\r\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    }
